    "The fundamental etiology of the disease remains unidentified, with the exception of a limited number of family instances attributable to genetic mutation.",
    "At present, there is an absence of therapeutic interventions for the disease, necessitating a solution for the substantial amounts of imaging data required to manage a significant number of patients.",
    "A crucial viewpoint is the examination of longitudinal data.",
    "Alzheimer's disease is a degenerative condition that develops gradually, and documenting the dynamic alterations is essential for comprehending its progression.",
    "Moreover, it is essential to tackle the obstacles related to restricted data accessibility in Alzheimer's disease research."
